<h4 id="when-did-you-start-writing-and-performing">When did you start writing and performing?</h4>
<p>I wrote my first poem when I was eight. It was about the moon, it was terrible. I knew I wanted to be a poet, or a professor, or involved in writing when I was about 16.</p>

<p>When I was 19, Dylan showed up with a literary magazine and a slam poem that he wanted to workshop. He then took me to some poetry slams in the Twin Cities and we started a poetry slam in our college. Now itâ€™s eight years later and itâ€™s my full time job.</p>

