<p>Writing, for me and for a lot of people, is therapy. Whenever Iâ€™m going through something in life, one of the first things I do is sit down and write a poem about it. For me, itâ€™s a method of processing, Iâ€™ve got all these emotions in my head and theyâ€™re big and terrifying, but if I can put them on a page and literally get them outside of my body I can be more objective about them, because I am looking at them and not just feeling them.</p>

